Just checked: node-fetch@2.0.0-alpha.5/lib/index.es.js has

```js
export { Headers, Request, Response, FetchError };export default fetch;
```

so `import fetch from 'node-fetch'` would definitely work with Rollup and [rollup-plugin-node-resolve](https://www.npmjs.com/package/rollup-plugin-node-resolve) with `module` option turned on.

lib/index.js has

```js
module.exports = exports = fetch;
exports.Headers = Headers;
exports.Request = Request;
exports.Response = Response;
exports.FetchError = FetchError;
```

so Babel would work as well.

@bitinn @TimothyGu 
I'm using Typescript to compile my code.
```typescript
import fetch from 'node-fetch';
```

will compile to

```javascript
var fetch = require('node-fetch').default;
```

but in `lib/index.js` does not export default
